summary: Can some people just deal with the fact the MCU is not the same as the comic book multiverse? People find it so hard to believe...
body: Can some people just deal with the fact the MCU is not the same as the comic book multiverse? People find it so hard to believe that Shuri is the smartest character in the movies or that Carol is god-level strong. They always use the “well you don’t read the comic books so you don’t know” line to make themselves feel superior. I understand your frustration because I feel the same way about the Game Of Thrones/ASOIAF show/books difference, but you cannot use comic book examples to argue about something that’s happened in the movies. Thanks for coming to my ted talk.

summary: Imagine Tony itching to tickle you when you wear a dress that exposes your ticklish waist. requested by: ticklish anon, of...
caption:
Imagine Tony itching to tickle you when you wear a dress that exposes your ticklish waist.

requested by: ticklish anon, of course!! <3
warnings: tickling, tony being a pain, a cheesy cinderella moment.

Tony always filled his parties with beautiful, successful people. But none of them compared to you.

He was mid-conversation when you finally came down the stairs from your apartment onto the party floor, and he forgot what he was saying. His gaze was pulled to you magnetically, watching as you focused on not falling down the stairs in your heels and dress, entirely unaware of your own Cinderella moment. Everyone was stunned.

Your dress was long and hung from your figure perfectly, a delicious crimson with gold lace details - a homage to your Iron boyfriend. Tony felt affection swell in his chest, his throat choked up and his eyes wanted to water. But he saved himself when he noticed your waist.

The dress left it bare, little slivers of skin on each of your sides. And Tony felt himself tingle all over. He’d have some fun with you tonight, but first…

“Ah, and here she is,” he smiled, opening his arms and going to meet you at the bottom of the stairs, his previous conversation forgotten.

You smiled bashfully as you felt his gaze float over you, admiring every detail, an arm enveloping your waist and pulling you into his side. He lowered his voice and pressed his lips to the shell of your ear, “You look… like my groupie.”

You couldn’t help the laugh that bubbled out of you at his words, “Oh, but I am.”

“Well I’m pretty lucky.” He kissed your temple and lead you into the crowds of the party, fingers brushing your waist. He took you back to the man he was speaking to before and apologised for leaving, pushing the light of attention onto you.

He waited until you were deep in business conversation with his acquaintance until he made his move.

His fingertips grazed over your bare waist quickly, causing you to seize up and jerk away from his hand. Your voice shot up an octave and your mouth pulled into a pained smile, slapping his hand away from your waist. And then, you tried to resume the conversation normally, as if he hadn’t just tickled and tried to embarrass you.

He raised a cheeky brow and glanced around the room full of important people that wanted to speak to you.

Oh, this would be fun.

summary: My favourite day! Can I have a Drabble with Tony not feeling well and he’s trying to rest for once, but nobody’s having it?...
question: My favourite day! Can I have a Drabble with Tony not feeling well and he’s trying to rest for once, but nobody’s having it? Thanks in advance if you decide to do this.
answer:
Tony should’ve gone back to his bedroom.  He should’ve taken his coffee mug and the fluffy blanket from the back of the couch and laid down in bed.

But no.  The allure of the 80-inch TV in the living room had won out, so that’s where he set up camp.  He’d swallowed a dose and a half of dayquil, then tipped his head back while half-listening to reruns of Scrubs.

“Hey, Tony?”  Bruce is out of breath, and he brings a strong smell of burning plastic that even Tony’s clogged nose can detect.  “Do you have a spare biohazard bin?  Mine melted.”

“What?”  Tony opens his eyes, unsure if this is for real or just a fever dream.  

“And I need a mop,” Bruce says.  

“Ok…”  Tony blinks at him, then rubs his eyes.  His head still aches.  “Ask Pepper.  She knows where everything is…”

“You ok?” Bruce asks, taking in Tony’s current home base.

“I’m trying to take a sick day,” Tony says, irritation feeding into his voice.

“Oh.  I knew something was up when you didn’t run downstairs to see the damage…”

“I have a cold, I’m not dead.”  Tony rolls his eyes.  Then, “Text me a picture?”

“Sure,” Bruce laughs.  “I can do that.”
